    dc:title "A new species of the genus Loricula Curtis from central Honshu, Japan (Heteroptera: Microphysidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736036>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736038>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736042>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736046>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736044>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736040> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736036>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Habitat (A, B) and habitus image of female adult (C) for Loricula mikawa sp. nov. (A–C) and L. miyamotoi Yasunaga & Yamada (D). A & B. Secondary evergreen broadleaf forest in Toyoda City where L. mikawa occurs. C. L. mikawa, female. D. Well-preserved deciduous forest, habitat of L. miyamotoi (Yamanashi Prefecture, Japan). D: Image courtesy of T. Ishikawa." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736036/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736038>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Habitus images of Japanese Loricula species (adult females). A–C. L. mikawa sp. nov. (A: dorsal view, B: ventral view, C: right lateral view). D. L. miyamotoi Yasunaga & Yamada, dorsal view. E. L. yakushima Yasunaga & Yamada, dorsal view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736038/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736042>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Scanning electron micrographs for Japanese Loricula species (adult females). A–C. L. mikawa sp. nov. D–F. L. miyamotoi. G, H. L. pilosella. I, J. L. yakushima. K, L. L. nikko. A, D, G, I & K. Anterior body, dorsal view. B, E & L. Ditto, left lateral view. C, F, H & J. Posterolateral process of pronotum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736042/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Compound microscopic images showing detailed morphology for L. mikawa sp. nov., female. A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Antenna. C. Labium. D. Thorax, ventral surface. E. Forewing base. F. Abdomen, ventral view. G. Apodemal process. H. Genital segments, ventral view. I. Three eggs found in abdomen (F)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736044>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Scanning electron micrographs for dorsal surface structure of female forewing (hemelytron). A. L. mikawa sp. nov. B. L. miyamotoi. C. L. pilosella. D. L. yakushima." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736044/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3736040>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Scanning electron micrographs for female of Loricula mikawa sp. nov. A. Dorsal habitus. B. Head, dorsal view. C. Anterior body, ventral view. D. Apex of labium, ventral view. E. Vestiture pattern on ventral surface of hemelytron. F. Scent efferent system. G. Protarsus and grooming comb. H. Mestatarsus. I. Apex of abdomen, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3736040/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

